BFN 

<F P=106> [Communique issued by the Guangdong Provincial Statistics </F>
Bureau on 8 March: "Statistical Report Issued by Guangdong 
Provincial Statistics Bureau on National Economic and Social 
Development in 1993"] 
  [Text] In 1993, the Guangdong people further put into 
effect the guidelines set by the 14th CPC National Congress by 
making greater strides in reform, opening to the outside world, 
and the modernization drive, thus enabling the national economy 
to continue to grow rapidly and make achievements in various 
social undertakings. According to preliminary statistics, gross 
domestic product in 1993 reached 314 billion yuan, up 21 percent 
over the previous year. Value added by secondary industry was 
155.9 billion yuan, up 33.3 percent, and that of the tertiary 
industry was 102.3 billion yuan, up 14.6 percent. The principal 
problems of economic development are relatively sharp price 
increases, an excessive scale of investment, and lagging 
agricultural development. 
<H5>  1. Agriculture </H5>
  In 1993, Guangdong vigorously developed a highly efficient 
type of farming which provides greater and better yields to 
boost the overall efficiency of agricultural production. As a 
result, the added value of agriculture in 1993 was 55.8 billion 
yuan, up 3 percent over the previous year, with the gross 
agricultural output value reaching 88.6 billion yuan, up 3.5 
percent. 
  Of staple agricultural products, peanut, vegetables, and tea 
registered greater production than in the previous year. 
Serious natural disasters and a reduced area under cultivation 
led to a reduction in the output of grain, sugar cane, hemp and 
the like, and fruit. 


