  Achievements were made in afforestation. In 1993, trees were 
planted over an area of 111,400 hectares. A total of 105 
counties (cities and districts) fulfilled the afforestation 
quotas assigned to them, thus enabling Guangdong to basically 
accomplish the task of making the whole province green two years 
ahead of schedule. Guangdong also made progress in developing 
and utilizing colophony, rosin, China fir, Chinese chestnut, and 
other forest products. 
  Animal husbandry grew steadily. As compared with the 1992 
figures, the 1993 outputs of principal livestock products and 
the numbers of animals on hand are as follows: 


